==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Otocyst
<hw>O"to*cyst</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Oto-</ets> +
<ets>cyst</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool. & Anat.)</fld> <def>An auditory cyst
or vesicle; one of the simple auditory organs of many invertebrates,
containing a fluid and otoliths; also, the embryonic vesicle from which
the parts of the internal ear of vertebrates are developed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Otography</ent>⟦br⟧
